    "body": "> `addPeer` adds the peer asynchronously so you have to wait some time for your list of peers to update. I think you're using the public ip of the nodes right? maybe it is some issue with your nat or router that doesn't allow incoming connections. You could try replacing the ip with \"127.0.0.1:30301\"\r\n\r\nI tested this private chain in my local network environment, so all the IPs are beginning with \"127.0.0.1\". As you say, I waited for minutes after addPeer, but it did not work either. \r\n\r\nAddition, below it is some output in terminal, `peercount` is changing sometimes. Also, before I `addPeer`, there is also `peercount=1` sometimes.\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO [09-30|15:48:47.433] Looking for peers                        peercount=1 tried=49 static=1\r\nINFO [09-30|15:48:58.266] Looking for peers                        peercount=0 tried=46 static=1\r\n``` ",
